" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 27 May 2026 01:26:39 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/new-discovery-rewrites-what-we-know-about-the-speed-of-light</guid></item><item><title>新发现缩短了通往密码相关量子计算机的道路</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/new-findings-shorten-the-road-to-cryptographically-relevant-quantum-computers</link><description>最近的两篇论文表明量子计算机可能比预期更快地破解现代密码学&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/new-findings-shorten-the-road-to-cryptographically-relevant-quantum-computers.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 27 May 2026 01:11:39 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/new-findings-shorten-the-road-to-cryptographically-relevant-quantum-computers</guid></item><item><title>大型强子对撞机检测到可能改写物理学的奇怪粒子行为</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/large-hadron-collider-detects-strange-particle-behavior-that-could-rewrite-physics</link><description>在欧洲核子研究中心大型强子对撞机工作的科学家们可能会看到标准模型之外的物理学迄今为止最强烈​​的暗示——标准模型是解释宇宙基本粒子和力的数十年历史的理论。通过研究被称为“企鹅衰变”的极其罕见的粒子转变，研究人员发现了与理论预测不完全相符的行为，从而增加了未知粒子或力量影响结果的可能性。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/large-hadron-collider-detects-strange-particle-behavior-that-could-rewrite-physics.webp" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 27 May 2026 00:56:39 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/large-hadron-collider-detects-strange-particle-behavior-that-could-rewrite-physics</guid></item><item><title>白鲸认出了镜子中的自己，通过了自我识别测试</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/beluga-whales-recognize-themselves-in-the-mirror-passing-the-self-recognition-test</link><description>对圈养白鲸的案例研究提供了该物种镜像自我识别的第一个潜在证据。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/beluga-whales-recognize-themselves-in-the-mirror-passing-the-self-recognition-test2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 27 May 2026 00:41:39 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/beluga-whales-recognize-themselves-in-the-mirror-passing-the-self-recognition-test</guid></item><item><title>洛斯阿拉莫斯国家实验室向国际空间站发送质谱仪</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/los-alamos-national-laboratory-sends-mass-spectrometer-to-international-space-station</link><description>AIMSS 有效载荷是作为国防部太空测试计划 Houston-11 任务的一部分在 SpaceX 第 34 次龙商业补给服务任务上发射的。照片由 LANL 提供&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/los-alamos-national-laboratory-sends-mass-spectrometer-to-international-space-station.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 27 May 2026 00:26:39 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/los-alamos-national-laboratory-sends-mass-spectrometer-to-international-space-station</guid></item><item><title>人工智能驱动的光谱仪芯片将实验室技术缩小到一粒沙子的大小</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/ai-powered-spectrometer-chip-shrinks-lab-technology-to-the-size-of-a-grain-of-sand</link><description>加州大学戴维斯分校的新型人工智能芯片可以使用足够小、几乎可以安装在任何地方的设备来分析光和化学物质。通过将智能硅传感器与机器学习相结合，它无需笨重的设备即可实现实验室式的光谱分析。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/ai-powered-spectrometer-chip-shrinks-lab-technology-to-the-size-of-a-grain-of-sand.webp" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 27 May 2026 00:11:39 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/ai-powered-spectrometer-chip-shrinks-lab-technology-to-the-size-of-a-grain-of-sand</guid></item><item><title>机器学习帮助天文学家在现有数据中找到 10,000 个新行星候选者</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/machine-learning-helps-astronomers-find-10000-new-planet-candidates-in-existing-data</link><description>行星隐藏在众目睽睽之下。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/machine-learning-helps-astronomers-find-10000-new-planet-candidates-in-existing-data.webp" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 26 May 2026 23:56:39 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/machine-learning-helps-astronomers-find-10000-new-planet-candidates-in-existing-data</guid></item></channel></rss>